The paper discusses algorithms for building minimax trees, which are a data structure used in various areas of computer science such as data compression, group testing, and circuit design. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to algorithms and data structures. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper specifically discusses algorithms for building minimax trees. 

cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the Kraft Inequality, which is a fundamental result in information theory. 

cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the time complexity of the algorithms for building minimax trees. 

cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as minimax trees have applications in geometric algorithms. 

cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper discusses the properties of minimax trees, which are a type of tree structure.
